==English==
===Etymology===
From the Greek ''[[μαγνήτης λίθος]]'' (magnítis líthos), magnesian stone.

===Noun===
'''magnet''' ([[magnets]])

#A piece of material that attracts some [[metal]]s by [[magnetism]].
#(''informal, preceded by a noun'') A person or thing that attracts what is denoted by the preceding noun.
#:''He's always in the company of women &mdash; he's a bit of a babe magnet.''

